    {
        "content": "<p>alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13017#discussion_r3066397899\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Technically the <code>AssertTryClone</code> here isn't appropriate where <code>Version</code> can have a <code>Vec&lt;String&gt;</code> (I think morally at least) via the build metadata and prerelease and such. That being said I don't think we're equipped to actually have any sort of fallible-allocation-handling path here at all in the sense of we can't fallibly create a <code>Version</code> (nor clone it).</p>\n<p>As a mild bikeshed on <code>AssertTryClone</code> though, to me that feels a bit too dangerous or a bit too easy to forget to handle allocation failure. Would a newtype wrapper for <code>Version</code> work instead? Something like a local-to-this-module <code>TryVersion</code> which is a wrapper around <code>Version</code></p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 584746782,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1775850049
    },
